&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;At &lt;a href=&quot;https://evolve.com/&quot;&gt;Evolve&lt;/a&gt;, we’re on a mission to make vacation rental easy for everyone. Our high-performing, customer-obsessed team runs on curiosity, communication, and accountability—working together to create exceptional experiences for our owners and guests. Whether solving big challenges, delivering outstanding results, or celebrating wins, we approach every day with purpose and passion. If you’re ready to join a mission-driven company where every teammate has the opportunity to thrive, Evolve might just be the place for you.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why this role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re building the acquisition engine that finds the right customers, converts them, and turns them into long-term subscribers — whether that&#39;s a serious short-term rental operator managing a portfolio of properties or an individual owner with a single listing. This role spans both motions: a higher-touch, segment-driven funnel for operators who want a full technology and service stack, and a self-serve, product-led motion for individual owners who need to get value fast and stick.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This PM owns that entire acquisition surface: from defining segment ICPs and funnel architecture to building the product features that drive conversion and activation. It&#39;s a growth role with deep product responsibility — you&#39;ll design experiments, ship features, own your metrics, and work directly with Marketing, Sales, and Engineering to move the number.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the acquisition product strategy across segments — define the funnel for both operator and single-owner acquisition, identify the conversion levers unique to each, and build the product experience that takes users from &quot;interested&quot; to &quot;activated.&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and run growth experiments end-to-end: write the hypothesis, scope the build, measure the result, make the call. Ship fast, kill fast, scale what works.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead discovery: talk to customers across the spectrum — from portfolio operators to first-time hosts — and translate those insights into a differentiated product roadmap.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Marketing and Sales on go-to-market execution — you own the product side of campaigns, not just the feature side.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and own your KPIs. Build dashboards, track cohorts, and report on acquisition and activation performance without delegating the analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring a technical perspective to every initiative — you can write a spec, debate an architecture tradeoff, and spot when an engineering estimate is off.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What makes you a great fit&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of product management experience, with meaningful time in acquisition, growth, or PLG roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You think in funnels. You&#39;ve owned conversion rate, CAC, activation rate, or similar metrics and moved them — ideally across more than one segment or acquisition model.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Growth-oriented: you&#39;ve run controlled experiments, built holdout groups, and made product decisions from the results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical depth: comfortable writing SQL, reading API docs, and working at the spec level with engineers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full-cycle PM experience — you&#39;ve taken products from discovery through research, spec, build, launch, and iteration.&lt;/li&gt;
